Pre-Game Insights: Cyprus have only lost one of their last five home games in the UEFA Nations League.
Others: Cyprus will welcome Kosovo to Larnaca for their Group C2 UEFA Nations League clash on Monday, buoyed by an impressive win on matchday one as they look to build momentum in the group.
Kosovo will be looking for redemption after suffering a demoralising 3-0 defeat to Romania in their first match of the campaign.
